sentence: Friday's session closes with the NASDAQ Composite Index reaching a historical high.
The index closed at 6,629.05 up 23.98 for the day.
The index had a previous high 6624.22002 on 10/18/2017.
The total shares traded for the NASDAQ was over 1.88 billion.
Advancers stocks led declining by 1.59 to 1 ratio.
There were 1817 advancers and 1140 decliners for the day.
On the NASDAQ Stock Exchange 152 stocks reached a 52 week high and 20 those reaching lows totaled.
The most active, advancers, decliners, unusual volume and most active by dollar volume can be monitored intraday on the Most Active Stocks page.
The NASDAQ 100 index closed up .27% for the day; a total of 16.2 points.
Celgene Corporation ( CELG ) had the largest percent change down (-10.76%) while PayPal Holdings, Inc. ( PYPL ) had the largest percent change gain rising 5.53%.
The Dow Jones index closed up .71% for the day; a total of 165.59 points.
Procter & Gamble Company (The) ( PG ) had the largest percent change down (-3.65%) while Boeing Company (The) ( BA ) had the largest percent change gain rising 2.2%.
